{{Infobox football biography | name = Yoan Gouffran | image = [[Image:Yoan Gouffran 7.jpg|200px]] | caption = | fullname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1986|5|25}} | birth_place = [[Villeneuve-Saint-Georges]], [[France]] | height = {{height|m=1.77}} | position = [[Winger (sport)|Winger]] | currentclub = [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] | clubnumber = 9 | youthyears1 = | youthyears2 = 2001â2003 | youthclubs1 = [[Red Star Saint-Ouen|Red Star Paris]] | youthclubs2 = [[SM Caen|Caen]] | years1 = 2003â2008 | years2 = 2008â | clubs1 = [[SM Caen|Caen]] | clubs2 = [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] | caps1 = 122 | caps2 = 121 | goals1 = 34 | goals2 = 16 | nationalyears1 = 2005â2008 | nationalteam1 = [[France national under-21 football team|France U-21]] | nationalcaps1 = 22 | nationalgoals1 = 3 | pcupdate = 29 May 2011 | ntupdate = 21 October 2007 }} '''Yoan Gouffran''' (born 25 May 1986 in [[Villeneuve-Saint-Georges]], [[Val-de-Marne]]) is a [[France|French]] [[football (soccer)|footballer]] of [[Guadeloupe]]an descent<ref>[http://www.ville-la-courneuve.fr/5_regards/journal.php?id=1212 Yoan Gouffran, footballeur professionnel au SM Caen]. Ville-la-courneuve.fr. Retrieved on 2011-07-26.</ref> who currently plays for [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Girondins de Bordeaux]] of the French [[Ligue 1]]. Gouffran plays as a [[Winger (sport)|Winger]] or rarely, as a [[striker]] and is renowned for his pace and ability to finish with either foot. Gouffran is allergic to grass, his allergy has been described by his coach as "embarrassing".<ref>[http://www.smh.com.au/sport/football/pitch-battle-ahead-for-french-footballer-allergic-to-grass-20101019-16rap.html Pitch battle ahead for French footballer allergic to grass]. Smh.com.au (2010-10-19). Retrieved on 2011-07-26.</ref>
==Career== On 20 May 2007, Gouffran was awarded French [[Ligue 2]] Player of the Season after a successful season with [[SM Caen]] which saw the club promoted to the [[Ligue 1]].<ref>[http://www.sport24.com/sport24-fil-info-actualite-sportive-news-football-gouffran-et-cassard-recompenses-58956.html French Ligue 2 Player of the season at Sport24]</ref> The 21-year-old was named Ligue 2 Player of the Year as he helped Caen seal promotion to the top flight of [[France|French]] football.
===Bordeaux=== After achieving success with Caen during the 2007â08 Ligue 1 season, it was suspected Yoan would make a move elsewhere. After constant rumors linking him primarily with [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], including rumors of him signing a pre-contract agreement with the [[England|English]] club,<ref>[http://www.oleole.com/blogs/arseole/posts/arsenal-sign-yoann-gouffran Arsenal sign Yoann Gouffran]. Oleole.com. Retrieved on 2011-07-26.</ref><ref>[http://www.eurosport.fr/football/ligue-1/2007-2008/sport_sto1456549.shtml Le journal du mercato â Ligue 1 2007â2008 â Football â Eurosport]. Eurosport.fr (2008-01-25). Retrieved on 2011-07-26.</ref> Gouffran opted to stay in Ligue 1, signing a four-year contract with [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Girondins de Bordeaux]]. The transfer fee was priced at [[Euro|â¬]]6.5 million and he officially joined the club on 30 June 2008.<ref>[http://www.mercato365.com/depeches/filinfo_246399_2514_Bordeaux-Gouffran-presente-le-30-juin.shtml Bordeaux Gouffran prÃ©sentÃ© le 30 juin]. Mercato365.com. Retrieved on 2011-07-26.</ref> After starting the [[Ligue 1 2008-09|league season]] off with no league goals after 26 matches, he finally scored his first league goal for Bordeaux on 29 April 2009 in a key match against [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]], which Bordeaux won 3â2.<ref>[http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008/2009&code_evt=D1&num_ordre=8&code_jr_tr=J33 Rennes v. Bordeaux Match Report]. Lfp.fr. Retrieved on 2011-07-26.</ref> On the final matchday of the season, May 30, he scored the winning goal that secured Bordeaux the championship, against his former club Caen who were relegated to [[Ligue 2 2009â10|Ligue 2]].<ref>[http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/30052009/3/joy-bordeaux-end-10-year-french-title-wait.html Joy as Bordeaux end 10-year French title wait]{{dead link|date=July 2011}}</ref>
Gouffran denied league leaders [[Paris Saint Germain|PSG]]'s attempt at winning seven straight [[2011-12 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] games, when he scored the equalizer in a 1-1 home draw on 6 November 2011.<ref>http://msn.foxsports.com/foxsoccer/ligue1/story/bordeaux-1-1-psg-ligue-1-match-day-sissoko-equalizer-match-report-110611</ref> The result meant that Bordeaux had drawn six of their first seven league games.<ref>http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=320275&cc=5901</ref>
===International career=== Gouffran is a [[France national under-21 football team|France U-21]] international. He took part in the [[UEFA U-21 Championship 2006|2006 U-21 Championships]] in [[Portugal]], where he made four appearances and scored one goal. So far, he has made 22 appearances with the U-21's, scoring three goals. He has yet to be called up to the [[France national football team|French senior team]].
